  "notes": "Tumbuka (chiTumbuka), Bantu N.21, Malawi and Zambia. Latin orthography: <b> and <d> are implosives /ɓ ɗ/; <ŵ> is the bilabial fricative /β/ (a distinctive Tumbuka letter); <c> = /tʃ/, <j> = /dʒ/; <l> and <r> are allographs of one flap phoneme /ɽ/; <ng'> = /ŋ/ vs <ng> = prenasalised /ŋɡ/. Five vowels /a ɛ i ɔ u/, plus syllabic /m̩/. Tumbuka has lost lexical tone in most varieties; tone is not written and is not modelled.",
